In this paper, we establish a blow up criterion for the short time classical
solution of the nematic liquid crystal ow, a simpli?ed version of
Ericksen-Leslie system modeling the hydrodynamic evolution of nematic liquid
crystals, in dimensions two and three. More precisely, $0<T_*<+\infty$ is the
maximal time interval i?ff (i) for $n=3$, $|\omega|+|\nabla d|^2\notin
L^1_tL^\infty_x(\mathbb R^3\times [0,T_*])$, and (ii) for $n=2$,
$|\nabla|^2\notin L^1_tL^\infty_x(\mathbb R^2\times [0,T_*])$.